1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the construction of Quantum LDPC codes and provides a lower bound on the minimum distance of the code. This falls under the purview of Information Theory. 
2. cs.QL (Quantum Physics): The paper deals with Quantum LDPC codes and their construction. This falls under the purview of Quantum Physics. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the Cayley graph of Fn and its use in constructing Quantum LDPC codes. This involves the study of data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the minimum distance of the Quantum LDPC codes and provides a lower bound. This involves the study of computational complexity. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Quantum LDPC codes have applications in cryptography and security. This falls under the purview of Cryptography and Security.
